arts.ttl: The lowdown on Millwall 1 Sunderland 1 - Azeez delights The Den home support with stoppage-time equaliser
arts.sum: Millwall: Jensen, Leonard, Hutchinson (Langstaff 90), Cooper, Bryan, Saville (Emakhu 90), De Norre, Honeyman (Bradshaw 46), Esse, Watmore (Azeez 74), Coburn (Ivanovic 77). Tom Bradshaw, Ryan Wintle, Azeez and Danny McNamara – all starters at Stoke City – made way for Joe Bryan, Duncan Watmore, Josh Coburn and George Honeyman.

arts.ttl: Millwall boss hails impact from subs - and keeper Jensen - as Lions salvage a point with late leveller
arts.sum: Neil Harris was delighted to see Femi Azeez open his goal account for Millwall with the late equaliser in today’s 1-1 draw at home against Sunderland. “All the subs contributed when they came on,” said Lions head coach Harris.

arts.ttl: ‘First half we were f****** useless’ - Millwall boss Harris breaks down 1-1 draw against Sunderland
arts.sum: Femi Azeez’s stoppage-time equaliser ensured that the Lions extended their unbeaten run to eight matches but they needed a vastly-improved second-half display to wipe out Aaron Connolly’s early opener. We looked like a team that could pass through and cut Sunderland open, we could play around the outside, run forward, play incisive passes and create chances.

arts.ttl: Millwall score in stoppage-time to hold Sunderland
arts.sum: Femi Azeez struck a late equaliser as Millwall earned a 1-1 Championship draw against leaders Sunderland in a match that was delayed following two medical emergencies in the crowd.

arts.ttl: Femi Azeez nets late leveller as Millwall draw against leaders Sunderland
arts.sum: The Black Cats are above second-placed Sheffield United on goal difference in the table

arts.ttl: Sunderland boss urges Chris Rigg, Jobe Bellingham to stay amid Man United, Borussia Dortmund interest
arts.sum: Sunderland boss Regis Le Bris urges Chris Rigg and Jobe Bellingham to stay at the club amid significant transfer interest in the pair.

arts.ttl: 'I knew I'd be a better man for coming back' - Millwall boss Neil Harris on dream Den return
arts.sum: Millwall legend Neil Harris agreed to an emotional return last year, following an SOS call from the Championship outfit, who have gone from strength to strength after avoiding relegation
